      "nextLessons": ["lesson-004"],
      "estimatedTime": 25,
      "content": {
        "text": "Now let's put together what we've learned and start reading Korean syllables.\n\nKorean syllables are formed by combining consonants and vowels in specific patterns. The most basic pattern is consonant + vowel.\n\nLet's practice reading some simple syllables.",
